I"ù<h2 id="aim">Aim</h2>
<p>To build a indoor map of a room/chamber(rough map) by mapping the relative distance of objects on a map.</p>

<!--more-->

<h2 id="hardware-used">Hardware Used</h2>
<ul>
  <li>1 ‚Äì Micro servo.</li>
  <li>1 ‚Äì Ultrasonic sound sensor.</li>
  <li>1 ‚Äì Arduino.</li>
  <li>1 ‚Äì An image of radar.
<img src="/site/assets/images/blog/Indoor-Radar/const.png" alt="Resistor" width="auto" height="auto" /></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="details">Details</h2>
<p>A Ultrasonic distance sensor is mounted over a servo, that keeps rotating. The distances in different directions are recorded and the value of angle and distance is sent to the computer.
<img src="/site/assets/images/blog/thumbnails/Indoor Radar Using Ultrasound.png" alt="Resistor" width="auto" height="auto" />
In the computer a cpp code shows a image that is manipulated according to the data recieved from the controller. Black dots will be put up for the objects traced as close as 50 cm or less.</p>

